<item>
            <title>[BEAM-1465] No natural place to flush resources in FileBasedWriter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-1465</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;FileBasedWriter&lt;/tt&gt; API does not have a natural place to flush resources opened by the writer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, if you create an &lt;tt&gt;OutputStream&lt;/tt&gt; in your &lt;tt&gt;Writer&lt;/tt&gt; using the &lt;tt&gt;FileBasedSink&lt;/tt&gt;&apos;s channel and this &lt;tt&gt;OutputStream&lt;/tt&gt; buffers outputs, there is no natural place to call its &lt;tt&gt;flush()&lt;/tt&gt; method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe something like &lt;tt&gt;finishWrite()&lt;/tt&gt; to match the existing &lt;tt&gt;prepareWrite(WritableByteChannel channel)&lt;/tt&gt; can work.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
